<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-30T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-30T19:00:00-05:00" n="121" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">339.3921L96/a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé des Affaires in the Dominican
                                    Republic</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Brewer</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-30T20:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                            1920—8 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>28. Department informed Amerigo Lugo and Fabio Fiallo and other
                                Dominican citizens have been imprisoned by Military Government for
                                infractions of censorship regulations, and that they are being tried
                                by special Court Martial. Advise Department fully at once regarding
                                this case.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>